doc_title: Morgan Chase has been on our radar for some time now. We did a hard pass in Jan. 2021 as it was too expensive and in March 2022 we suggested playing it defensively. We examine the last trade that made money despite
event_text: ["Outlook The combination of rapid monetary tightening; extreme food and energy inflation; alongside a steep fiscal cliff makes a recession almost a certainty in our view. Alongside that; the very tight labor market means that expenses will rise for most firms faster than revenues. We think JPM won't be able to dodge this and we expect lower earnings and lower multiples on its earnings in 2023."]

doc_title: The Microsoft Store Has the Xbox Series X in Stock for $500
event_text: ["The Microsoft Store itself currently has its flagship console. The scalpers and supply chain issues seem to have subsided just enough for you to grab one if you so please. doc_title: Qualcomm Is Plotting a Return to Server Market With New Chip
event_text: ["The last time it made such an attempt was 2017; when Qualcomm began selling an Arm-based server chip called the Centriq 2400. It relied on Samsung Electronics Co. to manufacture the products and said they outperformed Intel’s Xeon processors in energy efficiency and cost. At the public introduction of the server chip line in November of that year; potential customers such as Microsoft took to the stage to voice their interest in the offering."]

event_text: ["19 August 2022 by Business News ? DStv dropping the ball on video streaming problems : Nine months later; several DStv apps are still experiencing problems when trying to stream video from the pay-TV platform's servers. – MyBroadband ID documents and contact details exposed in Vodacom fibre reseller data breach : A marketing agency data breach has exposed the personal details and ID copies of Vodacom Fibre customers. – MyBroadband Scammers send phony Microsoft Office USBs that install malware : The baiting technique makes victims believe they mistakenly received an Office Professional Plus installation USB. – MyBroadband Chrome update patches high-severity security flaw exploited in the wild : Google advises Chrome users to update to the latest version to avoid any possibility of falling victim to a security vulnerability exploited in the wild."]

doc_title: Class Action : Law360 : Legal News & Analysis
event_text: ["In Auto Insurance Suit A federal judge in San Francisco has certified a class of Wells Fargo investors who claim they were harmed when the bank allegedly hid misconduct in its auto insurance practices. August 16; 2022 GE And Canon Reach $350K Settlement In Data Breach Suit General Electric Co. and a Canon Inc. subsidiary that GE used to store benefits files have agreed to pay GE employees whose financial information was exposed in a 2020 data breach up to $3;500 each out of a pool of $350;000 to end litigation filed in the wake of the episode. August 16; 2022 Asset Manager Exits $227M Stock Buy Class Action A California federal judge handed an investment management firm a win in a benefits suit originally involving KPC Healthcare Holdings Inc. that accused the companies of botching a $227 million purchase by KPC's employee stock ownership plan; ruling the workers couldn't prove the asset manager knew the conduct was unlawful."]
